observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the: 

a. BAC to use the PERT/CPM submitted by the contractor as basis for the preparation of SCC particularly in the number of days to complete the project;


b. Municipal Engineer to prepare the Statement of Time Elapsed and monitor the implementation of the projects based on the contract duration stipulated in the SCC. Moreover, compute the appropriate liquidated damages for the three projects not completed on or before the target completion date, and;

c. Municipal Treasurer to collect the applicable liquidated damages due from the contractors with negative slippage.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
BAC to use the PERT/CPM submitted by the contractor as basis for the preparation of SCC particularly in the number of days to complete the project;
Municipal Engineer to prepare the Statement of Time Elapsed and monitor the implementation of the projects based on the contract duration stipulated in the SCC. Moreover, compute the appropriate liquidated damages for the three projects not completed on or before the target completion date, and;
Municipal Treasurer to collect the applicable liquidated damages due from the contractors with negative slippage.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to require:

the Municipal Engineer to prepare PERT/CPM in the determination of number of days to complete the project in order to come up with a better estimate of labor cost;

the BAC to use the PERT/CPM submitted by the contractor as basis for the preparation of SCC particularly in the number of days to complete the project;

the Municipal Engineer to prepare the Statement of Time Elapsed and monitor the implementation of the projects based on the contract duration stipulated in the SCC. Moreover, compute the number of liquidated damages for the three projects not completed on or before the target completion date, and;

the Municipal Treasurer to collect the amount of liquidated damages due from the contractors with negative slippage.

We recommended that the management:


a.) Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO Designate with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;




b.) Require the inventory committee to conduct physical count of all its local road network system and prepare the Report on the physical Count of Road Network System;

c.) Require the GSO Designate to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete record of Road Network Property Cards for all roads in its component; and

d.) Require the Municipal Accountant to record back in the appropriate PPE accounts the Public Infrastructures appearing in the registries as of December 31, 2015, and

e).  disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the Local Road Network System of the municipality.

We recommended that management:

a.) Require the Municipal Engineer to prepare Report on Public Infrastructures and furnish a copy of said report to the Property and Accounting Offices;




b.) Require the Municipal Accountant to record in the books of accounts the eight (8) parcels of land with aggregate market value and assessed value of P6,742,246.64 and P773,300.00, respectively;  

c.) Require the Inventory Committee to include all parcels of land owned by the municipality in the physical count and report the same in the RPCPPE;

d.) Require the GSO Designate to undertake proper disposal of unserviceable properties;

 e.)	Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entry to derecognize from the books of accounts the value of unserviceable properties upon final disposal;

f.) Require the GSO Designate and the Municipal Accountant to maintain complete, accurate and updated Property Cards (PCs) and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELCs) respectively, and reconcile these records regularly;  

g.)	Require the Property Unit and the Accounting Office to effect the necessary adjustments in their records, if any, in order to reflect the correct balance of every PPE account; and

h.) Consider hiring/appointing a full time GSO.

We recommended that management:


a).  Require the Municipal Assessor to prepare and submit to the Municipal Treasurer Designate on or before the 31st of December of each year, an assessment roll containing the list of all persons whose real properties have been duly assessed or re-assessed and the value of such properties;

 b).  Require the Municipal Treasurer Designate to furnish the Municipal Accountant at the beginning of the year, a duly certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible during the year;

c).  Require the Municipal Accountant to draw JEVs to set up the RPT and SET Receivable at the beginning of the year based on the certified list submitted by the Municipal Treasurer in order to reflect the correct amount due and collectible from taxpayers;

d).  Require the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer Designate to correct their records on the amount of RPT and SET Receivables established at the beginning of the year for CY  2019 and previous years by adopting the assessment roll prepared by the Municipal Assessor in order to come up with the corrected balances of these accounts as of December 31, 2019 and submit to this office a certified schedule of such receivables; and

e).  Require  the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer Designate to regularly reconcile their records on RPT and SET Receivables and effect the necessary adjustment/s, if any.

